<subSubSection lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,150,2035]" lastBlockId="73.[151,1437,150,643]" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[631,861,1937,1963]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Mexican Lampfish</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[921,981,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="9.0">9 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1001,1072,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="3.5">3.5 in</quantity>
) SL (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California). British Columbia (
<bibRefCitation author="Gillespie, G. E." box="[1260,1428,1973,1999]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="ref282335" refString="Gillespie, G. E. (1993) An updated list of the fishes of British Columbia, and those of interest in adjacent waters, with numeric code designations. Canadian Technical Report Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 1918." type="book" year="1993">Gillespie 1993</bibRefCitation>
) to off southern 
<collectingCountry box="[373,459,2009,2035]" name="Mexico" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez-Grana" box="[474,804,2009,2035]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rodriguez-Grana" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="1455 - 1461" refId="ref317172" refString="Rodriguez-Grana, L., Herrera, G., Herrera, L. &amp; Castro, L. R. (2004) Divergence of two forms of Triphoturus in the eastern Pacific based on mtDNA cytochrome b gene sequence and larval morphology. Journal of Fish Biology, 64, 1455 - 1461. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 0022 - 1112.2004.00413. x" type="journal article" year="2004">
Rodríguez-Graña 
<emphasis box="[679,736,2009,2035]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
), including Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation author="De La Cruz-Aguero and Galvan-Magana" firstAuthor="De La Cruz-Aguero" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="25 - 31" refId="ref274229" refString="De La Cruz-Aguero, J. &amp; Galvan-Magana, F. (1992) Peces mesopelagicos de la costa occidental de Baja California sur y del Gulfo de California. Anales del Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, 19, 25 - 31." type="journal article" year="1992">De La Cruz-Agüero and Galván-Magaña 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Depth: surface to perhaps 
<quantity box="[765,859,151,177]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.882" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="2882.0">2,882 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[874,966,150,178]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8812743999999997" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="9453.0">9,453 ft</quantity>
) (min.: Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California; max.: Personal communication: Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History Fish Collection, Los Angeles, California). Maximum depth poorly known, most captures appear to be in 
<quantity box="[533,625,258,284]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[639,730,258,285]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.99744" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="3280.0">3,280 ft</quantity>
) or less. Deeper records, such as 
<quantity box="[1104,1197,258,284]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="4100.0">4,100 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1211,1316,258,285]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0989504" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="13448.0">13,448 ft</quantity>
) (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California), are based on the maximum depth fished by a midwater trawl and may represent a catch shallower than the maximum depth. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garman 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[198,596,365,391]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculeus">
<emphasis box="[198,421,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus oculeus</emphasis>
(Garman 1899)
</taxonomicName>
has been considered to be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gilbert, 1890" authorityName="Gilbert" authorityYear="1890" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1345,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus mexicanus</emphasis>
Gilbert, 1890
</taxonomicName>
. However, on the basis of both DNA and larvae characters Rodríquez-Graña 
<emphasis box="[1139,1196,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
(2004) separated the two species. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[342,567,436,462]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculeus">
<emphasis box="[342,567,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus oculeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found from 
<geoCoordinate box="[733,792,437,463]" degrees="13" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55555" value="13.0">13°N</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate box="[828,886,436,463]" degrees="35" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55555" value="-35.0">35°S</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
